      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"2. BUN UNDERCURRENT hit the ground running off the tricky draw last start and was never headed (25.83) at this track in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 over 450m. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Can continue the winning form. 1. LAMINATE has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 2.5 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 25.65 beating Prawn And Order. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from four attempts. Leading player again. 3. BLACK TYCOON turned in a solid run last start over 350m at Healesville finishing 5th and beaten only 4.5 lengths (19.71). Has the ability to give this a shake. 7. NAPIER BALE must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.\",\"runners\":[2,1,3,7],\"exclusive\":false}",
